<dl id="s17019b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="us17" href="#s17019b">Ithaca: </a><a href="../../FF/unbs/s17all.htm#s17019b">sector 19(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> aberration of light <small>Blue</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">When the telescope was applied to the observation of the fixed stars, it was found that each star underwent a series of small apparent variations in position, which repeated themselves with perfect regularity every year. This phenomenon is called the <mark>aberration of light</mark>. <small> Wentworth and Hill, <a name="TBOP" href="/udra/udex.htm#TBOP"><cite title="source">A Text-Book of Physics</cite></a> (1904), 378</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: See also <a name="s17027bq" href="s17all.htm#s17027bq">Sheet 17.027(bq)</a> for <cite>UG</cite> 17.1766f. </mm> </dd></dl>
